("5", "On every continent, in every country throughout the globe, education is slightly different. Although the same debates are had, for example, the best age at which to begin compulsory education and the perfect length for a school day, the answers various nationalities arrive upon vary greatly. It is nothing less than fascinating to delve into this data and it doesn’t take long before you realize that education around the world is ultimately different even though we all pretty much learn the same things."),
("5", "It is even more fascinating when you think about the fact that countries compare the education level of their population with other countries, something that seems impossible considering the different approaches. Education is a vital part of life, we can all agree on that, and that’s why learning more about it can be really beneficial to you and the way you learn things."),
("5", "In Australia, the School of the Air broadcasts lessons via radio signals to far-flung pupils living in remote areas."),
("5", "Of all the schools in the world, the largest is in India. It is called the City Montessori School and it has over 32,000 students."),
("5", "China is the country where kids get most homework. Teenagers in Shanghai do a staggering 14 hours a week at the kitchen table."),
("5", "The primary school is Phumachangtang, Tibet, is thought to be the highest school in the world at 5,373 metres above the sea."),
("5", "One of the subjects taught in Icelandic schools is knitting."),
("5", "America is where you’ll find the world’s oldest teacher, Agnes Zhelesnik, who is 101 years old."),
("5", "Because of the flooding problems faced by the country, Bangladesh has no fewer than 100 boat schools. Each one has internet access, a library and is solar powered."),
("5", "The country with the shortest school year and the longest school day is France."),
