("8", "Teas vs infusions. What is the difference? Technically, all tea is derived from the plant, Camellia sinensis. These teas include black, oolong, green, and white. Herbal “teas” such as peppermint, nettle, chamomile, etc. are really infusions. The herbs are steeped in water just like tea, but they don’t come from the tea plant. It is common to find blends that include tea and infusions."),
